  "prompt": "Is there a database with all nutritional information?",
  "response": "There are several comprehensive nutritional databases:\n\n1. USDA FoodData Central\n- Most comprehensive US food nutrition database\n- Free and publicly available\n- Contains detailed nutrient information for thousands of foods\n- Regularly updated\n- Available online at https://fdc.nal.usda.gov/\n\n2. SELF Nutrition Data\n- Extensive database with nutritional info\n- Allows searching and comparing foods\n- Provides detailed breakdown of nutrients\n\n3. MyFitnessPal Database\n- Large database for tracking nutrition\n- Good for diet and fitness tracking\n- Contains many branded and generic foods\n\n4. ESHA Food Composition Database\n- Professional-level nutrition database\n- Used by nutritionists and dietitians\n- More comprehensive but requires paid subscription\n\n5. NCCDB (Nutrition Coordinating Center Food Database)\n- Comprehensive research-level database\n- Used by many scientific studies\n- Maintained by University of Minnesota\n\n6. International databases:\n- Canada's nutrient file\n- European Food Information Resource (EuroFIR)\n\nThe USDA FoodData Central is generally considered the most reliable and comprehensive free resource for nutritional information.",
